    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Is C++ placement new supported in cython?\r\nI have seen usage of new but cannot find any mention of placement new.\r\nhttps://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/new#Placement_new\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\nI am trying to define a struct containing a c++ vector on the heap using malloc but accessing the contained vector causes a crash.\r\nI believe this is because the data has not been initialised correctly.\r\n\r\nDoes cython have a way of using the c++ placement new feature to initialise the vector attribute in the existing structure?\r\n\r\n## Ideal solution\r\nCython would add a way to use this feature if it does not exist already.\r\n\r\n## Alternatives\r\nThis can be achieved by using an extern block but this is a rather janky workaround.\r\n```cy\r\ncdef extern from *:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\ntemplate <typename T>\r\nvoid placement_new(T* t) {\r\n    new(t) T();\r\n}\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    void placement_new(cpp_type*) nogil\r\n```",
    "closed_at": null,
